                    statement: "The common ion effect is the decrease in solubility of a sparingly soluble salt caused by the addition of a soluble salt that shares one of the same ions",
                    leChatelierLink: "Adding a common ion shifts the dissolution equilibrium left (Le Chatelier) → less solid dissolves → lower solubility"
