        // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
        keyTakeaways: [
            "Entropy quantifies the number of accessible microstates via S = k_B ln(W)",
            "The Second Law states ΔS_universe ≥ 0 for all real processes",
            "The Third Law establishes S = 0 for a perfect crystal at 0 K — the absolute entropy reference",
            "Spontaneity is determined by ΔS_universe, not just ΔS_system",
            "Entropy increases: solid < liquid << gas; with temperature; with molecular complexity",
            "Standard reaction entropy: ΔS°_rxn = Σ nS°(products) - Σ nS°(reactants)",
            "Phase transition entropy: ΔS = ΔH_transition / T_transition",
            "Heating entropy: ΔS = nCₚ ln(T₂/T₁)",
            "Gas expansion entropy: ΔS = nR ln(V₂/V₁)",
            "Biology and engineering examples show entropy governs all real processes"
        ]
