                        trend: "Down a group: bond strength decreases → acid strength increases",
                        examples: ["HF < HCl < HBr < HI (bond energies: 568, 432, 366, 298 kJ/mol)"],
                        note: "HF is anomalously weak despite having the most polar H–F bond because the bond is very strong"
