                        "n(HCl) excess = 6.25 × 10⁻³ mol (NaOH titrates remaining HCl 1:1)",
                        "n(HCl) consumed by CaCO₃ = 0.06000 − 6.25 × 10⁻³ = 0.05375 mol",
                        "CaCO₃ + 2HCl → CaCl₂ + H₂O + CO₂",
                        "n(CaCO₃) = 0.05375 / 2 = 0.02688 mol",
