                    "3. Ethanol has an O−H bond → O−H is a H-bond donor; lone pairs on O are acceptors → ethanol forms intermolecular H-bonds",
                    "4. Dimethyl ether: oxygen has lone pairs (H-bond acceptor) but NO N−H, O−H, or F−H bond → cannot donate H-bonds → no H-bonding between ether molecules",
