                    "2. In ice: each O forms exactly 4 H-bonds in a regular tetrahedral lattice (hexagonal structure)",
                    "3. The ice tetrahedral lattice holds molecules further apart and in a more open arrangement than liquid water",
                    "4. Ice density = 0.917 g/cm³; liquid water at 0°C = 0.9998 g/cm³ → ice is less dense",
                    "5. Biological importance: ice floats on water → lakes and rivers freeze from the top down; ice layer insulates liquid water beneath → aquatic organisms survive winter under ice",
