                    "2. Hydration enthalpy (~−784 kJ/mol total) is large enough to compensate for lattice energy (+787 kJ/mol)",
                    "3. Entropy of dissolution (disorder increases) also drives dissolution → NaCl dissolves in water",
                    "4. In hexane: nonpolar C−H bonds cannot form ion-dipole forces with Na⁺ or Cl⁻",
                    "5. Energy released by hexane-ion interactions << lattice energy → insufficient energy to break lattice",
                    "Result: NaCl dissolves in polar water (ion-dipole forces comparable to lattice) but not in nonpolar hexane (no compatible IMFs)"
