                        "Discovery of the electron (Thomson, 1897): atoms contain negative subcomponents",
                        "Discovery of the nucleus (Rutherford, 1911): atoms have dense, positive cores",
                        "Discrete line spectra (Balmer, 1885): atoms emit/absorb light at only specific wavelengths",
