                    "3. Meso forms exist when C2 and C4 have opposite configurations and C3 bridges them",
                    "4. Systematic analysis: (2R,3R,4R), (2S,3S,4S) are enantiomers; (2R,3S,4R) is meso; (2R,3R,4S) and (2S,3S,4R) are enantiomers; (2R,3S,4S) and (2S,3R,4R) are enantiomers",
                    "Result: 6 stereoisomers total (not 8) due to meso forms"
